WEBVTT

00:02.069 --> 00:05.371
STEVEN:
We are known for our spirits,
but this is new activity.

00:05.373 --> 00:10.175
For whatever reason, the mirror
freaks a lot of people out.

00:10.177 --> 00:12.511
Do you have something
against women?

00:12.513 --> 00:14.079
[ Door creaks ]

00:14.081 --> 00:15.781
[ Gasps ]

00:15.783 --> 00:17.750
I felt something
pressing on my throat.

00:17.752 --> 00:19.518
Choking you?
Yeah, like trying
to choke me.

00:19.520 --> 00:22.087
Oh, my God.
Is there something in here?

00:22.089 --> 00:23.689
There is something.

00:23.691 --> 00:26.925
♪♪

00:26.927 --> 00:28.761
[ Crows cawing ]

00:28.763 --> 00:32.464
When the dead are forgotten,
they become restless.

00:32.466 --> 00:34.633
Oh, my God!
You just touched me.
What? I did not touch you.

00:34.635 --> 00:36.301
I'm Amy Bruni.

00:36.303 --> 00:39.471
A haunting encounter
redefined my life.

00:39.473 --> 00:42.908
I live with that experience
and seek answers to the unknown.

00:42.910 --> 00:44.977
It says, "I am."

00:44.979 --> 00:46.712
I'm Adam Berry.

00:46.714 --> 00:49.882
At Gettysburg, the shadows
and screams of dead soldiers

00:49.884 --> 00:52.151
turned me
into a supernatural believer.

00:52.153 --> 00:53.685
Oh, my God.

00:53.687 --> 00:56.889
Together, our investigations
bring peace to the living...

00:56.891 --> 00:59.024
You can't scare us,
you can't deter us.

00:59.026 --> 01:01.026
...by giving a voice
to the dead.

01:01.028 --> 01:02.928
I'm going to ask you
one more time.

01:02.930 --> 01:04.430
What is your name?

01:04.432 --> 01:07.332
Because we believe the dead
and the living are all...

01:07.334 --> 01:09.501
kindred spirits.
Kindred spirits.

01:10.805 --> 01:12.905
BERRY:
Gettysburg, Pennsylvania,

01:12.907 --> 01:15.207
site of the Civil War's
bloodiest battle

01:15.209 --> 01:19.144
and where over 5,000 soldiers
lost their lives.

01:19.146 --> 01:22.247
Today, people come to Gettysburg
to relive the past

01:22.249 --> 01:26.251
but also to experience the many
ghosts who inhabit the town.

01:26.253 --> 01:28.387
Many can be found
at the Farnsworth House,

01:28.389 --> 01:31.023
a popular inn built in 1810.

01:31.025 --> 01:33.492
Once occupied by
Confederate soldiers,

01:33.494 --> 01:36.195
it's now a historic landmark
and museum,

01:36.197 --> 01:39.765
attracting both Civil War buffs
and paranormal thrill-seekers.

01:39.767 --> 01:41.633
But in the last three months,

01:41.635 --> 01:43.969
a malevolent presence
seized control,

01:43.971 --> 01:46.338
terrifying the tour guides
and guests,

01:46.340 --> 01:49.675
and they've called Amy and I
to figure out why.

01:49.677 --> 01:51.510
There's been
so much more activity

01:51.512 --> 01:54.179
happening in the past few months
than ever before,

01:54.181 --> 01:56.248
especially in the basement and
attic, and they don't know why.

01:56.250 --> 01:58.217
Well, I mean, obviously,
Gettysburg is haunted.

01:58.219 --> 02:01.420
We've investigated it.
We have verified that.

02:01.422 --> 02:03.489
But this kind of dark haunting
that's happening

02:03.491 --> 02:05.357
at the Farnsworth House
is super-concerning,

02:05.359 --> 02:07.126
especially because
they have so many people

02:07.128 --> 02:10.262
coming in from outside
doing investigations and tours.

02:10.264 --> 02:12.431
Absolutely.
Well, let's go meet
with these guys

02:12.433 --> 02:14.333
and see what
they can tell us.
Yeah.

02:14.335 --> 02:17.369
BRUNI: We're meeting with
a couple of storytellers

02:17.371 --> 02:21.807
who give guided tours
dressed in period clothing.

02:21.809 --> 02:23.876
They claim the recent
paranormal activity

02:23.878 --> 02:27.880
they're experiencing
has become dangerous.

02:27.882 --> 02:30.249
Well, we got here
as quickly as we could.

02:30.251 --> 02:32.985
Sounds like things
have kind of ramped up.

02:32.987 --> 02:36.955
They have, indeed,
especially in the basement.

02:36.957 --> 02:40.058
We're known for about
14 different spirits,

02:40.060 --> 02:42.094
but this is new activity.

02:42.096 --> 02:43.929
I had two gals leave
just the other day.

02:43.931 --> 02:45.330
Yeah. Really?
Oh, really?

02:45.332 --> 02:46.365
And they said,
"We love your tour,

02:46.367 --> 02:47.499
but we got to get
out of here."

02:47.501 --> 02:49.168
And it's from
in the basement?
Yeah.

02:49.170 --> 02:50.769
Why don't we head down there
and take a look

02:50.771 --> 02:51.970
and see what's going on?
Yeah, yeah.

02:51.972 --> 02:53.539
All right, cool.
Okay.

02:53.541 --> 03:00.245
♪♪

03:00.247 --> 03:02.447
You said there were a number
of known entities in the house,

03:02.449 --> 03:04.750
but who do you think
is the new presence?

03:04.752 --> 03:07.920
STEVEN: I think it may be
a curmudgeonly,

03:07.922 --> 03:10.122
older Confederate soldier.

03:10.124 --> 03:11.423
Hmm.
Huh.

03:11.425 --> 03:13.759
So, he tends to not
like women very much.

03:13.761 --> 03:15.060
Okay.

03:15.062 --> 03:18.397
One in particular
was another storyteller.

03:18.399 --> 03:20.265
She looked
a little uncomfortable

03:20.267 --> 03:22.834
and got up and moved
to the other side.

03:22.836 --> 03:25.270
She said, "Something
was pinching my arm."

03:25.272 --> 03:27.773
And she said, "But when I moved,
it didn't quit."

03:27.775 --> 03:30.375
And she pulled up her sleeve
and had pinch marks on her arm.

03:30.377 --> 03:32.010
Has that always been the case,

03:32.012 --> 03:33.212
or is that happening
more often now?

03:33.214 --> 03:34.913
It's happening
more often.

03:34.915 --> 03:36.548
This all sounds
pretty disturbing.

03:36.550 --> 03:40.252
Anything else you can tell us
about what's going on down here?

03:40.254 --> 03:44.723
STEVEN:
Well, we've got a mirror that
seems to have a weird effect.

03:44.725 --> 03:48.627
The mirror has a lot
of different stories.

03:48.629 --> 03:51.029
When they put it
in the cellar,

03:51.031 --> 03:54.533
they'd been having some strange
things show up in the mirror.

03:54.535 --> 03:57.469
Men will look in the mirror, and
it won't be their reflection.

03:57.471 --> 03:59.271
Okay.
People will take photos

03:59.273 --> 04:02.207
and have things show up
in the mirror.

04:02.209 --> 04:04.142
I was just here
a couple weeks ago.

04:04.144 --> 04:05.711
A lady was standing
in front of the mirror,

04:05.713 --> 04:07.779
and her husband was
taking a photograph of her,

04:07.781 --> 04:09.081
and when he showed me
the photo,

04:09.083 --> 04:10.882
she had a black smile
across her face.

04:10.884 --> 04:13.852
Weird. Interesting.
It was very strange.

04:13.854 --> 04:16.722
Many believe mirrors
can be used as a tool

04:16.724 --> 04:19.324
for the deceased to
communicate with the living,

04:19.326 --> 04:22.394
but others believe mirrors
have more sinister powers,

04:22.396 --> 04:24.496
acting as portals
that allow entities

04:24.498 --> 04:26.965
to enter and exit our world.

04:26.967 --> 04:28.967
We'll just have to figure out
where it came from.

04:28.969 --> 04:31.103
It was from
a local estate sale.

04:31.105 --> 04:32.871
BERRY: In Gettysburg?
In Gettysburg.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.840
Okay.
Okay, so when did it
get moved down here?

04:34.842 --> 04:36.375
July-ish?

04:36.377 --> 04:37.909
Like July, as in just
a few months ago?

04:37.911 --> 04:40.812
Of this year, mm-hmm.
Okay.

04:40.814 --> 04:44.983
Activity seems to be happening
around the mirror,

04:44.985 --> 04:47.386
and there's been attacks
against women.

04:47.388 --> 04:49.221
It's possible the two
are connected,

04:49.223 --> 04:52.190
but we really won't know
until we start investigating.

04:52.192 --> 04:56.528
♪♪

04:56.530 --> 04:59.965
BERRY: The Farnsworth activity
isn't limited to the basement.

04:59.967 --> 05:02.634
They're also having problems
in the attic.

05:02.636 --> 05:05.137
BRUNI:
So, what about the activity
up here? What happened?

05:05.139 --> 05:07.906
Ladies pinched, poked,
their hair tugged on.

05:07.908 --> 05:09.141
Mm-hmm.

05:09.143 --> 05:11.109
I've had women up here
who felt like something

05:11.111 --> 05:14.112
was leaning on their back.
Really?

05:14.114 --> 05:16.214
People hearing men talking.

05:16.216 --> 05:18.283
Something leaned up,
and I could, like,

05:18.285 --> 05:22.087
literally feel the breath on
my face, and it said, "Get out."

05:22.089 --> 05:26.224
So, it sounds like another space
where women experience more?

05:26.226 --> 05:27.993
I think so.

05:27.995 --> 05:29.861
Were there Confederate soldiers
stationed up here?

05:29.863 --> 05:33.265
Absolutely.
This is where the sniper

05:33.267 --> 05:37.035
who killed Jennie Wade
was positioned.

05:37.037 --> 05:38.837
BRUNI: Jennie Wade
was a local resident

05:38.839 --> 05:40.872
tragically killed
by a stray bullet

05:40.874 --> 05:45.077
during the Battle of Gettysburg
and the only civilian casualty.

05:45.079 --> 05:47.346
Presumably, the bullet
that killed Jennie

05:47.348 --> 05:49.414
came from this very attic.

05:49.416 --> 05:53.118
That sniper would have been
right at that window.

05:53.120 --> 05:54.786
There's only about a foot
and a half there,

05:54.788 --> 05:57.923
so I imagine he's lying down
with his rifle,

05:57.925 --> 06:01.760
poised, firing up
at the Yankees up the street.

06:01.762 --> 06:04.696
BERRY:
I mean, I feel like there's
a lot of different buildings

06:04.698 --> 06:06.164
in this area
that are connected,

06:06.166 --> 06:09.134
specifically this building
and the Jennie Wade house.

06:09.136 --> 06:11.069
Everything here
is connected.

06:11.071 --> 06:14.139
And whatever is here does seem
like it's getting darker.

06:14.141 --> 06:15.440
Yes.

06:15.442 --> 06:18.577
It's starting to pinch people
and threaten them and --

06:18.579 --> 06:19.945
Pull their hair.
It's getting physical.

06:19.947 --> 06:21.346
Right.
Yeah, it's getting physical.

06:21.348 --> 06:22.781
That's a problem
when you have a place like this

06:22.783 --> 06:24.483
that's kind of
a tourist attraction.

06:24.485 --> 06:27.352
You're kind of like, "Well,
what am I subjecting them to?"

06:27.354 --> 06:28.920
BERRY:
Also, what actually is it?

06:28.922 --> 06:30.489
Is it a soldier,
or is it something

06:30.491 --> 06:32.090
that's a bit more negative?

06:32.092 --> 06:33.692
Is there anybody else
that we could talk to

06:33.694 --> 06:35.327
about the property?
Sure.

06:35.329 --> 06:36.995
I'm sure I can get someone
to come in

06:36.997 --> 06:38.463
and talk to you
about the property.
All right, great.

06:38.465 --> 06:40.198
We'll try to figure out
why things are getting

06:40.200 --> 06:41.800
a little more extreme
around here.

06:41.802 --> 06:43.668
All right.
Thank you, guys.
Thank you.

06:43.670 --> 06:46.171
BRUNI: Kayla put us in touch
with Cindy,

06:46.173 --> 06:48.673
one of the owners
of the Farnsworth House.

06:48.675 --> 06:52.010
We want to see what information
she has regarding the mirror.

06:52.012 --> 06:54.513
♪♪

06:54.515 --> 06:58.917
Everyone seems so interested
in the mirror in the basement.

06:58.919 --> 07:01.720
I do know that,
for whatever reason,

07:01.722 --> 07:03.989
the mirror freaks
a lot of people out.

07:03.991 --> 07:05.157
Okay.

07:05.159 --> 07:06.825
In particular, I have
one storyteller

07:06.827 --> 07:09.995
who really doesn't
like the mirror,

07:09.997 --> 07:14.332
and she is the most bothered
down there by the spirits.

07:14.334 --> 07:17.035
I mean, physically bothered.

07:17.037 --> 07:20.105
She had to leave because
there's a spirit down there

07:20.107 --> 07:21.940
that doesn't want her
down there.

07:21.942 --> 07:24.910
The family who bought the
mirror, who was that, exactly?

07:24.912 --> 07:27.078
The Shultz family.
This is a family-run business.

07:27.080 --> 07:29.214
Okay. And are they
still accessible?

07:29.216 --> 07:30.682
Yes. Yes.
They are?

07:30.684 --> 07:32.551
Well, maybe we can, like,
ask them exactly

07:32.553 --> 07:34.753
if they remember
when they bought it or where.

07:34.755 --> 07:36.154
Yeah.

07:36.156 --> 07:38.223
BRUNI: Before Adam and I do
any research on this mirror

07:38.225 --> 07:42.227
or anything else,
we need to start investigating.

07:42.229 --> 07:45.197
If there's an aggressive entity
here that's targeting women,

07:45.199 --> 07:48.700
we need to stop it
before it gets any worse.

07:48.702 --> 07:52.637
BERRY:
The staff is gone for the night,
leaving us alone with the mirror

07:52.639 --> 07:54.840
and whatever's behind
this dangerous activity.

07:54.842 --> 07:56.575
I think right now,
we just need to

07:56.577 --> 07:58.910
try to get some answers
or some direction.

07:58.912 --> 08:01.780
We're going to start tonight's
investigation in the basement

08:01.782 --> 08:03.949
with a few
different experiments.

08:03.951 --> 08:07.452
So, maybe EVP, spirit box,
flashlights.
Yeah.

08:07.454 --> 08:08.820
Flashlights.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.388
We're setting up flashlights
to see

08:10.390 --> 08:13.358
if any entities
can turn them on and off.

08:13.360 --> 08:15.494
We're also going to do
a spirit box session.

08:15.496 --> 08:17.929
Spirits can use the device
to speak with us.

08:17.931 --> 08:22.801
I will ask questions while Amy
listens for any responses.

08:22.803 --> 08:25.303
As soon as you put
the headphones on your ears,

08:25.305 --> 08:27.772
I'm going to count to 10
and start.

08:27.774 --> 08:29.875
She'll use
noise-canceling headphones

08:29.877 --> 08:33.144
and cover her eyes to increase
her level of concentration.

08:33.146 --> 08:35.247
She can't hear me
while we do the session.

08:35.249 --> 08:38.517
5, 4, 3...

08:38.519 --> 08:39.618
Can you hear me?

08:39.620 --> 08:42.254
...2, 1.

08:42.256 --> 08:45.190
Is there anybody in this room
that would like to speak to us

08:45.192 --> 08:47.325
today through this device?

08:47.327 --> 08:49.628
Can you please
talk to her?

08:49.630 --> 08:52.430
We've been asked to come here
to find out

08:52.432 --> 08:56.868
why the activity is ramping up
and still going on.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.837
Shh.

08:58.839 --> 09:00.739
I'm sorry,
am I being too loud?

09:02.743 --> 09:05.810
Who is in here?
What's your name?

09:05.812 --> 09:08.513
What's your connection
with the building?

09:08.515 --> 09:11.249
Why?

09:11.251 --> 09:13.752
This is our opportunity
to find out who you are.

09:13.754 --> 09:15.921
Can you tell us
who you are?

09:17.925 --> 09:19.925
Can you try to turn on
that flashlight?

09:19.927 --> 09:21.793
Oh!
Yes.

09:21.795 --> 09:23.328
I did.

09:23.330 --> 09:26.698
Something just grabbed me
and, like, yanked me over.

09:26.700 --> 09:28.867
What do you want to tell us
about the mirror?

09:28.869 --> 09:30.335
You never know.

09:30.337 --> 09:31.603
So it's intelligent.

09:31.605 --> 09:33.505
Whatever is here
is intelligent.
Absolutely.

09:33.507 --> 09:35.640
Uh...
BRUNI: Is there something
in here?

09:35.642 --> 09:37.809
There is something.

09:37.811 --> 09:39.644
Right here?

09:49.790 --> 09:54.426
♪♪

09:54.428 --> 09:56.261
BERRY: We're in the basement
of the Farnsworth House

09:56.263 --> 09:58.196
in Gettysburg, Pennsylvania.

09:58.198 --> 10:01.199
An unknown spirit is
physically harassing women,

10:01.201 --> 10:03.234
making it unsafe
for visitors.

10:03.236 --> 10:06.404
We're using the spirit box
and flashlights to get answers.

10:06.406 --> 10:09.374
Amy can only hear the messages
coming through the spirit box.

10:09.376 --> 10:12.677
Can you tell us
who you are?

10:12.679 --> 10:14.913
Can you try to turn on
that flashlight?

10:14.915 --> 10:16.748
Oh!
BRUNI: Yes.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.351
I did.

10:19.353 --> 10:21.620
Okay, I saw you
do the blue one.

10:21.622 --> 10:25.323
♪♪

10:25.325 --> 10:28.460
Why do you pick on women?
Who's picking on the women?

10:28.462 --> 10:32.263
Is there something going on
with this mirror?

10:32.265 --> 10:36.201
'Cause people say they see
weird things inside this mirror.

10:36.203 --> 10:38.503
It's great.

10:38.505 --> 10:39.804
What's great?

10:39.806 --> 10:42.240
Come on.
You can talk to us.

10:43.577 --> 10:45.644
Anything else you want to
tell us about the mirror?

10:45.646 --> 10:47.679
Maybe.
Okay.

10:47.681 --> 10:50.115
What do you want to tell us
about the mirror

10:50.117 --> 10:52.283
or about anything
in this building?

10:54.321 --> 10:56.021
You never know.

10:56.023 --> 10:59.157
What are you saying to me?
"You never know" what?

10:59.159 --> 11:01.526
What does that mean?
What the [bleep] does that mean?

11:01.528 --> 11:02.527
Shh.

11:02.529 --> 11:03.862
Ugh!

11:03.864 --> 11:05.430
Listen.

11:05.432 --> 11:12.037
♪♪

11:12.039 --> 11:13.838
Ohh.

11:13.840 --> 11:16.041
[Bleep]

11:16.043 --> 11:18.309
Did it make any sense?

11:18.311 --> 11:20.412
Yeah, there was
a bunch of stuff.
Really?

11:20.414 --> 11:24.649
I said, "Could you twist
the flashlight on?"

11:24.651 --> 11:28.386
And then blue came on,
and then you said, "Yes."

11:28.388 --> 11:30.088
Weird.
Yeah.

11:30.090 --> 11:31.756
I said, "Is there anything else
you want to tell us

11:31.758 --> 11:34.492
about the mirror,"
and you said, "Maybe."

11:34.494 --> 11:36.861
I mean, these are, like,
conversations.
Really?

11:36.863 --> 11:38.763
It's familiar with the activity
in the house,

11:38.765 --> 11:40.365
and it knew what
the flashlights were,

11:40.367 --> 11:43.068
and it turned it on
and said, "Yes."
So it's intelligent.

11:43.070 --> 11:45.036
Whatever is here
is intelligent.
Absolutely.

11:45.038 --> 11:47.338
♪♪

11:47.340 --> 11:49.207
Whatever's in the basement
is smart

11:49.209 --> 11:51.109
and aware
of its surroundings.

11:51.111 --> 11:53.778
That also means
it could have a strategy.

11:53.780 --> 11:55.313
But we're going to move
up to the attic

11:55.315 --> 11:58.149
and see if the activity there
is as strong as the basement.

11:58.151 --> 12:00.652
We'll start off by using
our voice recorder

12:00.654 --> 12:03.254
to see if any spirits
want to communicate.

12:03.256 --> 12:07.092
Well, we're here in the attic
of the Farnsworth House,

12:07.094 --> 12:09.461
and we're looking
for anyone up here

12:09.463 --> 12:11.896
who might want to
have a chat with us.

12:11.898 --> 12:14.499
♪♪

12:14.501 --> 12:16.367
BERRY: During the Civil War,
somebody was up here

12:16.369 --> 12:18.036
and was shooting
out this window.

12:18.038 --> 12:19.738
Do you know
who that is?

12:19.740 --> 12:23.441
♪♪

12:23.443 --> 12:26.211
Do you have something
against women?

12:26.213 --> 12:29.748
♪♪

12:29.750 --> 12:31.816
Are you trying to get
their attention?

12:31.818 --> 12:34.319
♪♪

12:47.200 --> 12:49.667
Well, nothing up here
is talking.

12:49.669 --> 12:51.803
No.
Not at all.

12:51.805 --> 12:54.205
BRUNI: There have been claims
of harassment towards women

12:54.207 --> 12:56.474
in both
the basement and the attic,

12:56.476 --> 12:58.743
but the paranormal responses
we're getting

12:58.745 --> 13:00.879
are all coming
from the basement.

13:00.881 --> 13:02.147
The question is, why?

13:02.149 --> 13:03.648
Is it because of the mirror,

13:03.650 --> 13:06.117
or is it because of something
completely unrelated?

13:06.119 --> 13:09.020
Let's go regroup.
Yeah, and we'll
get a game plan.

13:09.022 --> 13:11.956
Sounds like we're going to have
to work a little harder here.

13:11.958 --> 13:14.425
BERRY: Because the activity
from last night

13:14.427 --> 13:16.795
didn't give us a name
or any new information,

13:16.797 --> 13:18.463
we're going to focus
on the mirror.

13:18.465 --> 13:19.631
The only thing we know is that

13:19.633 --> 13:21.266
it was purchased
at an estate sale

13:21.268 --> 13:24.369
by the owners of the
